{{Infobox journal | title = American Journal of Ancient History | cover = AmJAncHistcover.gif | editor = [[T. Corey Brennan]] | discipline = [[Ancient history]], [[classical studies]] | former_names = | abbreviation = Am. J. Anc. Hist. | publisher = [[Gorgias Press]] | country = | frequency = Annually | history = 1976-present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.gorgiaspress.com/bookshop/c-90-american-journal-of-ancient-history-0362-8914.aspx | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = | link2-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 609930711 | LCCN = | CODEN = | ISSN = 0362-8914 | eISSN = }} The '''''American Journal of Ancient History''''' (often abbreviated ''AJAH'') is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] covering [[ancient history]] and [[classical studies]]. It was established in 1976 at [[Harvard University]]<ref>"Curriculum Vitae", [http://classics.rutgers.edu/people/79-people-t-corey-brennan Rutgers: People - faculty - T. Corey Brennan] (Accessed October 9, 2013)</ref> and is published by [[Gorgias Press]]. The journal is abstracted and indexed by ''[[L'Année philologique]]''.<ref>See [http://www.annee-philologique.com/files/sigles_fr.pdf LISTE DES PÉRIODIQUES DÉPOUILLÉS] (Accessed October 9, 2013) or [http://www.ebscohost.com/academic/lannee-philologique L’Année philologique | Ancient Greek and Roman Studies | EBSCO] (Accessed October 9, 2013)</ref> The [[editor-in-chief]] is [[T. Corey Brennan]] ([[Rutgers University]]).
