{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}} {{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}} {{Infobox building | name = Batik Painting Museum Penang | native_name = [[Malay language|Malay]] : Muzium Lukisan Batik Pulau Pinang | image = Batik Painting Museum Penang.JPG | address = 19 [[Armenian Street, George Town|Armenian Street]], 10200 [[George Town, Penang|George Town]], [[Penang]] | location_town = [[George Town, Penang|George Town]], [[Penang]] | location_country = [[Malaysia]] | iso_region = | coordinates = {{coord|5.414934|100.337778|region:MY-07|display=inline,title}} | start_date = | completion_date = | architect = | owner = Tan Chong Guan | cost = | floor_area = 3 | top_floor = | floor_count = 650&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup><ref name="theedgegalerie">{{cite web|url=http://www.theedgegalerie.com/?p=3796|title=Homage to batik painting &#124; The Edge Galerie|publisher=theedgegalerie.com|accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref> | website = | embedded = {{designation list | embed=yes | designation1 = WHS | designation1_date = 2008 <small>(32nd [[World Heritage Committee|session]])</small> | designation1_type = Cultural | designation1_criteria = ii, iii, iv | designation1_number = [http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/1223 1223] | designation1_free1name = Region | designation1_free1value = [[List of World Heritage Sites in Southeast Asia|Asia-Pacific]] }} | references = | map_type = Malaysia Penang George Town central | map_caption = Location within [[George Town, Penang|George Town]]'s [[UNESCO]] [[World Heritage Site]] (purple) | building_type = Museum | architectural = | roof = | observatory = | elevator_count = | structural_engineer = | main_contractor = | opening = 1 October 2013 | management = }}
The '''Batik Painting Museum Penang''' ({{lang-ms|Muzium Lukisan Batik Pulau Pinang}}) is a museum about [[batik]] in [[George Town, Penang|George Town]], [[Penang]], [[Malaysia]].<ref name="timeout">{{cite web|url=http://www.timeout.com/penang/attractions/event/title/Penang-Heritage-Trust-Site-Visit-Batik-Penang-Museum|title=Penang Heritage Trust Site Visit: Batik Penang Museum - Attractions - Time Out Penang|publisher=timeout.com|accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref>
==History== The building was purchased in 2010 and underwent a three-year renovation before it was opened on 1 October 2013.{{cn|date=May 2017}}
==Architecture== The museum is located in a three-story [[Straits Settlements|Straits]] eclectic-style shop house.{{cn|date=May 2017}}
==Exhibition== There are around 80 batik paintings being exhibited in the museum.<ref name="visitpenang">{{cite web|url=http://visitpenang.gov.my/portal3/penang-tourism-news/1816-batik-painting-museum.html|title=Batik Painting Museum|publisher=visitpenang.gov.my|accessdate=12 March 2014}}</ref> The Museum showcases the earliest batik paintings done in the 1950s by the 'Father of Batik Painting' Chuah Thean Teng in Penang and the subsequent works by other Malaysian artists. Currently there are now 80 batik paintings by 25 artists in display. A small international section is included. Visitors will be able to view an excellent collection of magnificent batik paintings not to be seen anywhere else. This is definitely the only batik painting museum in Malaysia, and possibly in the world.
